issues.description: The problem statement and solution expect a method named `feedAllAnimals()`, but the template’s `Main.java` calls `farm.feed()`. This inconsistent method name will prevent students from mapping the requirement (`feedAllAnimals()`) to the code and compiling the provided `main` test harness.
issues.suggested_fix: Rename the call in `Main.java` from `farm.feed()` to `farm.feedAllAnimals()` (or, if you prefer shorter name, rename the method in `Farm.java` to `feed()`) so that the method name matches the problem description and solution implementation.
